      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EXTRAVAGANTLY (1) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.75) at this track behind Compton Bowie in a TG1-4W. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Makes plenty of appeal. COMPTON ZIRCONIA (8) looks close to another win after finishing second from Box 2 last time (23.67) at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Must be included in calculations. ROSE CHAMPAGNE (2) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 2 length third (22.51) in a Bottom Up - Restricted Win at Warrnambool. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Leading chance. MISTY AUTUMN (7) cannot be ruled out.",
